# Package: fpga-npu
# Version: 1.0.0

# Debian package control file
Source: fpga-npu
Section: misc
Priority: optional
Maintainer: FPGA NPU Team <npu-team@example.com>
Build-Depends: debhelper (>= 9), cmake (>= 3.10), gcc, linux-headers-generic
Standards-Version: 4.1.3
Homepage: https://github.com/example/fpga-npu
Vcs-Git: https://github.com/example/fpga-npu.git
Vcs-Browser: https://github.com/example/fpga-npu

Package: fpga-npu
Architecture: amd64
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}, linux-image-generic
Recommends: fpga-npu-devel
Description: FPGA Neural Processing Unit drivers and runtime
 This package provides kernel drivers and runtime libraries for
 FPGA-based Neural Processing Units (NPUs). It includes:
 .
 * Kernel driver module for NPU device management
 * User-space runtime library for NPU operations
 * Command-line utilities for device management
 * System service for NPU monitoring
 .
 The NPU provides hardware acceleration for neural network
 inference and training workloads.

Package: fpga-npu-devel
Architecture: amd64
Depends: fpga-npu (= ${binary:Version}), ${misc:Depends}
Description: Development files for FPGA NPU
 This package contains development files for building applications
 that use the FPGA NPU:
 .
 * Header files for the NPU API
 * Static libraries for linking
 * CMake configuration files
 * Code examples and tutorials
 * API documentation
 .
 Install this package if you want to develop applications that
 use the FPGA NPU for neural network acceleration.

Package: fpga-npu-docs
Architecture: all
Depends: ${misc:Depends}
Description: Documentation for FPGA NPU
 This package contains comprehensive documentation for the FPGA NPU:
 .
 * User guide and installation instructions
 * API reference documentation
 * Developer guide and architecture overview
 * Performance tuning guide
 * Tutorial and example code
 .
 The documentation is available in HTML format and can be
 viewed with any web browser.

Package: fpga-npu-dbg
Architecture: amd64
Section: debug
Priority: extra
Depends: fpga-npu (= ${binary:Version}), ${misc:Depends}
Description: Debug symbols for FPGA NPU
 This package contains debug symbols for the FPGA NPU packages.
 .
 Install this package if you need to debug applications that
 use the FPGA NPU or if you want to report bugs with meaningful
 stack traces.